Estimates from the global abortion costs 464,000 sexually transmitted infections and 173,000 new cases of HIV, largely because of unsafe abortion practices.[78] A knowledge, attitudes and practices survey conducted between January 2001 and February 2002 found that only 58.3% of men and 48.8% of women were aware of emergency contraceptives, and 28.5% of women reported ever having had a pregnancy ending in an induced abortion, indicating a prevalence of about 0.76% per year.[79]
